{"lemma":"أَصْداء","slug":"أَصْداء","root":"ص.د.#","root_slug":"ص-د-_","root_link":"/words/roots/ص-د-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n23906","n23910","n23914","n24051","n24056"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D8%B5%D9%92%D8%AF%D8%A7%D8%A1"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of صَدِيَ (ṣadiya) (form I): extreme thirst","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"echo"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/sˤa.dan/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n23906","headword_ar":"صُدَّى","root":"Sd","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A species of fig, white without, black within, and very sweet."},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHn, M, TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n23910","headword_ar":"صَدِيَ","root":"SdA^","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, L, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (L,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SadaA^N","text_ar":"صَدَاٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M,) said of a horse, (K, TA,) and of a kid, (S, TA,) [or a goat,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was of the colour termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SudoA^ap","text_ar":"صُدْاَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sorrel inclining to blackness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"blackness intermixed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tinged over, with redness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a colour like that of the rust of iron;"},{"kind":"text","text":"probably from the same verb in the sense next following]; (S, M, L, K, TA;) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Saduw^a","text_ar":"صَدُوَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA; [and it is implied in the K that the latter verb is syn. with the former in all its senses;]) but the former verb is that which is commonly known, and that alone which is required by analogy as a verb denoting a colour, and the latter is not known to have been heard; (MF, TA;) and in the L it is said that the verb in this sense is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sadiy^a","text_ar":"صَدِيَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiS~adaA^a","text_ar":"اِصَّدَاَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", this latter [formed from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiSoTadaA^a","text_ar":"اِصْطَدَاَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiSotadaA^a","text_ar":"اِصْتَدَاَ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AifotaEala","text_ar":"اِفْتَعَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b2-  Also, (M, K,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sadiy^a","text_ar":"صَدِيَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, Msb, K,) aor. as above, (S, Msb, TA,) and so the inf. n., (S, TA,) said of iron,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, rusty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rusted;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Msb, K;) in which sense it is said also of the like of iron. (M.)       -A2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sadiy^a","text_ar":"صَدِيَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"said of a man,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He stood erect, and looked."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SadaA^a AlmiroA=pa","text_ar":"صَدَاَ المِرْا=ةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sado'N","text_ar":"صَدْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TK,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He polished the mirror,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,) i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"removed from it the rust,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in order to use it as a collyrium;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sad~aA^ahaA","text_ar":"صَدَّاَهَا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taSodiy^apN","text_ar":"تَصْدِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) [Whether the mirrors"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1660},{"kind":"text","text":"of the Arabs were made of bronze, or of what other metal they were made, is not said. See also 1 in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HlA^","text_ar":"حلا"},{"kind":"text","text":".]       -A4-  And, aor. as above, said of an owl,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He uttered a cry"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cries."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sh, TA. [See also art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sdw","text_ar":"صدو"},{"kind":"text","text":".])"}],"source_refs":["S","M","L","K","TA","Msb","TK"]},{"entry_id":"n23914","headword_ar":"صَدِيٌ","root":"SdA^","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[part. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sadiy^a","text_ar":"صَدِيَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.]. ―         -b2-  One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yadiY mina AlHadiydi Sadiy^apN","text_ar":"يَدِى مِنَ الحَدِيدِ صَدِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"My hand is disagreeable in smell"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the rust of iron"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa SaAgirN Sadiy^N","text_ar":"هُوَ صَاغِرٌ صَدِيٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is one to whom disgrace,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shame, and baseness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"meanness, attach."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.) ―         -b4-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSodaA^u","text_ar":"اَصْدَاُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n24051","headword_ar":"صَدِىَ","root":"SdY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, Mgh, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaSodaY","text_ar":"يَصْدَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SadFY","text_ar":"صَدًى"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He thirsted:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Mgh, Msb, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he thirsted vehemently."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SadaA","text_ar":"صَدَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SadowN","text_ar":"صَدْوٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 2, in two places."}],"source_refs":["S","M","Mgh","Msb","K"]},{"entry_id":"n24056","headword_ar":"صَدًى","root":"SdY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[sometimes written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SadFA","text_ar":"صَدًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An echo;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~adaY","text_ar":"الصَّدَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what the mountain returns to him who utters a sound,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"voice,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cry, therein;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the sound of the mountain and the like that responds to one;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what responds to one with the like of his voice,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cry, in the mountains &c."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sam~a SadaAhu","text_ar":"صَمَّ صَدَاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His echo became dumb,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"may his echo become dumb"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S, TA;) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he perished,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"may he perish:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S and K and TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sm","text_ar":"صم"},{"kind":"text","text":":) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSam~a A@ll~`hu SadaAhu","text_ar":"اَصَمَّ ا@للّٰهُ صَدَاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"May God make his echo to return no sound"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S, K, TA;) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"may God destroy him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, and TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sm","text_ar":"صم"},{"kind":"text","text":":) for when a man dies, the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SdY","text_ar":"صدى"},{"kind":"text","text":"hears not from him anything, that it should respond to him. (S. [See also another explanation of this saying in what follows.]) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A sound, voice,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cry,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA,) in an absolute sense. (TA.) ―         -b3-  Also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part of the head,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M,) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part of the brain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which is the place"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"seat"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of hearing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA.) And therefore one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSam~a A@ll~`hu SadaAhu","text_ar":"اَصَمَّ ا@للّٰهُ صَدَاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"May God render deaf the part of his brain which is the seat of hearing"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b4-  And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"brain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K, TA,) itself. (TA.) And The ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"entire"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contents"},{"kind":"text","text":"(lit. the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stuffing,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ha$ow","text_ar":"حَشْو"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the head;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K, TA;) also called the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"haAmap","text_ar":"هَامَة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SadaEa A@ll~`hu SadaAhu","text_ar":"صَدَعَ ا@للّٰهُ صَدَاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"May God crack his brain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the contents of his head"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (M.) ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A bird that cries in the"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1671},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"haAmap","text_ar":"هَامَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"head"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the slain when his blood has not been avenged by retaliation:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a bird that comes forth"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from his head,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino raA^osihi","text_ar":"مِنْ رَاْسِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", M,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the head of the slain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when he,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, has become consumed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"decayed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K,) also called the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"haAmap","text_ar":"هَامَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M;) accord. to the assertion of the people of the Time of Ignorance; (M, K;) mentioned by A 'Obeyd; and some of them used to say that the bones of the dead became a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"haAmap","text_ar":"هَامَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", which flew: pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSodaA='N","text_ar":"اَصْدَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) and [this may be meant by the saying that it signifies] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"male of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buwm","text_ar":"بُوم"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K, TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"haAm","text_ar":"هَام"},{"kind":"text","text":": pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSodaA='N","text_ar":"اَصْدَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M:) they used to say that when a man was slain and his blood was not avenged by retaliation, there came forth from his head a bird like the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buwmap","text_ar":"بُومَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"haAmap","text_ar":"هَامَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", the male being called the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SdY","text_ar":"صدى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and it cried upon his grave,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AisoquwniY AisoquwniY","text_ar":"اِسْقُونِى اِسْقُونِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Give ye me to drink, give ye me to drink,"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning, of the blood of the slayer]; and if the slayer was slain, it abstained from its crying: (TA:) and [it is said that] it signifies also the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"body"},{"kind":"text","text":"[itself]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a human being after his death;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K;) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"remains of the dead in his grave,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"juv~ap","text_ar":"جُثَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"corpse"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Jm, TA.) ―         -b6-  And, (K,) accord. to El- 'Adebbes, (S,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A cricket;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain flying thing, that creaks by night, and hops,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and flies, thought by the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"common"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"people to be the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"junodab","text_ar":"جُنْدَب"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"but it is only the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SdY","text_ar":"صدى"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jndb","text_ar":"جندب"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being smaller than the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SdY","text_ar":"صدى"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S. [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~ar~aAru","text_ar":"الصَّرَّارُ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) ―         -b7-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain fish, black, long,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and bulky:"},{"kind":"text","text":"n. un."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SadaApN","text_ar":"صَدَاةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b8-  And [A man]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"small,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"slender, in person;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AA, M, K, TA;) and so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SadaA^o","text_ar":"صَدَاْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"'","text_ar":"ء"},{"kind":"text","text":", as mentioned by Az. (TA. [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SadoEN","text_ar":"صَدْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SadaEN","text_ar":"صَدَعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) ―         -b9-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Knowing in respect of what is conducive to the good of cattle:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SadaY maAlK","text_ar":"صَدَى مَالٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means thus: (M:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gentle in the management of cattle;"},{"kind":"text","text":"like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_izaA='u maAlK","text_ar":"اـِزَا=ءُ مَالٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":": so in the Jm: (TA:) or, as some particularly say, of camels: (M, TA:) [i. e.] you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahu laSadaY A_ibilK","text_ar":"اـِنَّهُ لَصَدَى اـِبِلٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily he is knowing in respect of camels, and of what is conducive to their good."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.)       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thirst:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vehement thirst:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) [see the first paragraph, in which it is mentioned as an inf. n.:] it is said that thirst does not become vehement but the brain dries, and therefore the skin of the forehead of him who dies of thirst cracks. (TA.) ―         -b2-  See also the next paragraph.       -A3-  And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"act of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mutaSad~iY","text_ar":"مُتَصَدِّى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K, TA,) i. e., [as is indicated in the M,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of him who raises his head and breast, looking towards,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"regarding, a thing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SadaApN","text_ar":"صَدَاةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["M","TA","K","S"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}